Happy International Pilates Day!

What started as a personal journey to heal, strengthen, and reconnect with my body… has now become a path to help others do the same.

✨ Pilates came into my life when I needed grounding — as a woman, a mother, and a mover.
It taught me how to listen to my body, honour its rhythm, and embrace both strength and softness.

Today, I get to share this beautiful practice with so many of you — helping people move pain-free, improve posture, build core strength, and most importantly, feel at home in their bodies again.

Every class I teach, every transformation I witness — reminds me why I chose this path.

To everyone who has been part of my Pilates journey — thank you for trusting me

And if you haven’t experienced the magic yet, my mat is always open for you!

Here’s to mindful movement, breath, and finding strength in stillness.

With love,
Shilpa

Did you know your facial muscles need just as much activation as your body muscles? 💆‍♀️✨

👉 Balloon Face Tapping
This gentle tapping boosts microcirculation, helps reduce smile lines, and promotes clearer, glowing skin by enhancing lymphatic flow and oxygen supply to the skin.

Together, these techniques help:

Tension headache? Jaw clenching? Dull skin?

You might need a good temporal massage 💆🏻‍♀️✨

In this face yoga practice, I’m guiding you through a relaxing temporal massage—a gentle yet powerful technique that targets the temples (the sides of your forehead), helping you release built-up tension from your face, scalp, and jaw.

🌀 Why practice temporal massage regularly?
✔️ Reduces stress and anxiety
✔️ Relieves tension headaches
✔️ Releases tightness from jaw clenching and teeth grinding
✔️ Boosts blood circulation to bring a natural glow
✔️ Helps tone the skin around eyes and temples
✔️ Encourages lymphatic drainage and relaxation

It’s a self-care ritual I absolutely swear by, especially after long workdays or screen time overload. Add this to your daily face yoga routine and feel the difference in just a few days 🌸

✨ Reminder: Face yoga is powerful, but pairing it with a wholesome diet and a consistent workout routine will elevate your results from within. Your glow starts with how you treat yourself—inside and out! 💖
.

Want a naturally chiseled jawline?

It starts with something we often overlook—lymphatic drainage. 💆‍♀️💧

In today’s reel, I’m showing you how to do a simple jawline massage as part of your face yoga routine. 

This gentle, intentional movement helps:

✨ Drain excess fluids that cause puffiness
✨ Define and sculpt the jawline
✨ Boost blood circulation
✨ Promote a healthy glow from within

Your lymphatic system doesn’t have a pump—it relies on movement. By stimulating these pathways with the right massage technique, you encourage your body to detox naturally, reduce water retention, and enhance muscle tone.

Pair this practice with:
🥗 A clean, anti-inflammatory diet
🚶‍♀️ Daily movement
💦 Plenty of hydration

And you’ll start noticing not just a sharper face—but a more refreshed you. 🌿

Tired eyes and deep smile lines?🫩

Your face is trying to tell you something—it’s time for some mindful movement!

In today’s reel, I’m showing you simple face yoga techniques that help:
✨ Reduce the appearance of sunken eyes
✨ Soften nasolabial folds (aka smile lines)
✨ Improve blood circulation
✨ Boost collagen naturally

These exercises wake up your facial muscles, increase oxygen flow, and bring a natural glow—no filters needed! Consistency is key, and just a few minutes a day can make a big difference in the long run.

But here’s a gentle reminder—face yoga alone isn’t enough.
For visible, lasting results, pair it with:

Your face reflects how you treat your whole body. Let’s glow from the inside out!
